CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 22, 1941, pg. 9 reads: "Pretty Co-Eds To "Date" Kappas At Regional Here The Week-End - All fraternals and no play will make Kappas dull, indeed. So local committees arranging for the regional confab here this week-end have asked pretty co-eds and debs to help make the gay note gayer at the several social affairs planned.  The pretties above are, left to right: First row, Grace Greenleaf, Inez Womack, Pearl Paylor, Elizabeth Lee, Eva Ruth Greenlee, Florine Robinson; second row, left to right, Marion Walker, Ruth Gloster, Roberta Douglass; third row, Marion Bayless."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left, first row: Grace Greenleaf, Inez Womack, Pearl Paylor, Elizabeth Lee, Eva Ruth Greenlee, and Florine Robinson; second row: Marion Walker, Ruth Gloster, and Roberta Douglass; third row: Marion Bayless, posed in interior with table in foreground and one window in background
